```json
{
"application": "SLURM",
"software": [
"python",
"mpirun",
"aveSat.py",
"sat_check_QI.py",
"interpolator.py",
"sat_check.py"
],
"resources": [
"MPI",
"SLURM_SUBMIT_DIR",
"SLURM_PMIX_DIRECT_CONN_UCX",
"UCX_TLS",
"I_MPI_PMI_LIBRARY",
"MASKFILE",
"ORIGDIR",
"CHECKED_DIR",
"WEEKLY_DIR1km",
"WEEKLYDATES",
"WEEKLY_DIR_24",
"DAILY_DIR_24",
"INPUTDIR",
"PYPATH",
"WEEKLY_1KMDIR",
"WEEKLY_16DIR",
"CLIM_FILE"
]
}
```
This script is running under the SLURM workload manager. The script utilizes various software including Python, mpirun, and several custom scripts like aveSat.py, sat_check_QI.py, interpolator.py, and sat_check.py. It accesses various resources including MPI environment variables, SLURM environment variables, file paths for input/output data, and custom environment variables like PYPATH.
